questionList.questionText: The Mona Lisa is a portrait of Lisa del Giocondo, a member of the Gherardini family of Florence, Italy.
The Earth is the only planet in the solar system that has liquid water on its surface.
The process of photosynthesis occurs in the liver of plant cells.
The element with the atomic number 1 is helium.
The periodic table is organized based on the increasing atomic mass of the elements.
The circumference of a circle is equal to 2 times the radius plus pi.
The law of conservation of energy states that energy cannot be created or destroyed, only transformed from one form to another.
The derivative of a function is the slope of the normal line to the function at a given point.
The process of digestion begins in the stomach with the action of hydrochloric acid.
The respiratory system is responsible for exchanging gases between the body and the environment.
